    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the submission based on the ValidationResults from the 2024-Q3 campaign without recognising that the current model of record (2026-q1-build-7) differs from the model configuration under which those results were generated (2024-q3-build-2). All 13 credibility factors were reviewed; 7 were assessed with achieved levels below required levels and 6 were flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite the pervasive shortfalls, the team concluded that the 2024 validation evidence was sufficient, overlooking the multi-year model version drift that renders the evidence non-applicable to the current build. This acceptance decision is erroneous and constitutes the targeted W-AR-04 weakness.",
